main event: A bright, white or gray object was observed moving rapidly in the sky for 18 minutes on April 29, 1965 in Washington, D.C.
interesting points: The object appeared to flash, strobe, and pulse in its brightness.
The object was estimated to be as bright as the brightest star in the sky.
The object made no sound and disappeared slowly, as if fading away.
The witness reported the object moving in front of and behind trees and shrubs.
The witness provided a sketch showing the object's motion and position in the sky.
sighted object: a bright, round object in the sky
